<h1>The Poppy</h1>
<h2>Why Do We Wear Poppies?</h2>
<p>Poppies are used to remember those who have served in the war because they are the flowers that grew on the battlefield after the end of WW1.</p>
<h2>”In Flanders Field”</h2>
<p>During the spring of 1915,after losing a friend,Canadian doctor Lieutenant Colonel John McCrae was inspired by the poppies grown in the fields to write the famous poem called “In Flanders Fields.” After WW1, the poppy began to be used as a symbol of Remembrance.</p>
